HEADWORD: Tempera
<hw>Tem"pe*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Paint.)</fld> <def>A mode or process of painting;
distemper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term is applied especially to early Italian
painting, common vehicles of which were yolk of egg, yolk and white of
egg mixed together, the white juice of the fig tree, and the
like.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Temperable</ent>⟦br⟧
